FT  16 APR 93 / UK Company News: Ashley to sell Spanish food arm
Ashley Group is selling Digsa, the Spanish food retailing operation, to
Parafax, for a deferred cash consideration of Pounds 20m and the assumption
of net debt of Pounds 33m.
Parafax is a Hong Kong company formed for the purpose of acquiring retail
companies by a consortium of investors, among whom are Sir Ralph Halpern and
Sir Michael Sandberg.
Ashley does not expect to pay a final dividend. It said the level of
activity across the group's non-food businesses remained encouraging.
